Feminized marijuana seeds

Introduction to Feminized Cannabis Seeds

What makes Feminized Cannabis Seeds â€œfeminizedâ€? Cannabis plants, like other plats, can be male or female. Male plants grow pollen sacs and can produce pollen. These pollen sacs are like small clusters of balls or pods. Female plants on the other hand produce flowers, often called buds.

These Buds are covered in rich sticky resin, full of cannabinoids and terpenes. The buds are what most growers are growing their own marijuana for. Duo to this reason, growers usually want to avoid male plants because they can pollinate your female plants.

When a female plant is not pollinated, it can focus its energy in producing the most dense and resin covered buds. But when a male plant pollinates them. They will stop producing flowers and start making seeds. Which ruins the highly soft after dense buds. This is why most growers remove their male plants and with feminized seeds, you won't have to worry about male plants because these seeds will only produce female plants.

Stable Genetics for Guaranteed Female

Stability is everything for feminized seeds. You don't want the risk of accidentally growing a male plant, which can ruin your whole crop. Our true feminized genetics are carefully selected and cultivated over many generations to ensure that each seed will grow into a healthy female plant.

Our Breeders work with legendary parent lines and test every batch to eliminate any chances of having unwanted males or hermaphrodites. This eliminates the chances of your female plants getting pollinated and potentially ruining your grow. Growing Feminized Seeds will give you peace of mind with guaranteed harvest!

Autoflower or Feminized Seeds

Both our Autoflower and Feminized seeds are actually Feminized. The correct question would be Autoflower or Photoperiod seeds. But feminized seeds is often used to refer to photoperiods. When we are talking about Autoflowers vs Feminized seeds, what we are really talking about is Autoflowers vs Photoperiod. Either way, here are some reasons why you would like to try growing autoflowers.

Autoflowering seeds are perfect if you are looking for a quicker turn around. For some, it's also a bit easier to grow because you don't have to rely on light cycles to start the flowering phase. And with our great genetics, these autoflowers can give you a large harvest without the hassle.

Feminized seeds, on the other hand, gives you more control over your grow. You can keep your plant longer in vegetative phase, and start flowering when you feel like it's the perfect time. This gives you room to shape your plant with training techniques, which often results in higher yields.

In practice, both types of seeds are used by many growers. Auto's for convenience and faster turn around to cover up the gaps while growing the perfect Feminized Cannabis plant.

Differences Between Indica and Sativa Feminized Seeds

Cannabis seeds come in both Indica and Sativa varieties. Both need soil, water, and light. But you will notice differences between the variants. For example, Indica plants tend to grow shorter and bushier with denser buds. And Sativa variants, on the other hand, grow much taller and grow airier buds.

You should also look into the differences in effects of Indica and Sativa strains. Indica strains tend to have a more relaxing experience, and Sativa strains offer more energizing and uplifting effects. For growers who are looking for a more balanced experience. You should try our hybrid variants. Our growers enjoy these because hybrid strains combine the best of both worlds, if you are not looking for the more extreme effects.

How To Cultivate Feminized Cannabis Seeds

Growing Feminized Seeds Indoors

Growing indoors gives you full control of the grow environment. This means you can get a more consistent and predictable result. You get to decide the temperature, humidity and light cycles. You don't need much to start growing indoors, but with the right equipment you can get professional results from your own grow room.

Growing Feminized Seeds Outdoors

Growing outdoors allows your plants to take full advantage of sunlight and space to reach their true natural potential. With healthy soil, airflow and enough direct light, your plants will grow large and provide heavy yields. Main benefit is that all you require is some space and seeds. No expensive equipment required. Although you will have to watch out for mother natures littles bugs, birds and molds. Keep your ladies safe, and they will reward you with a bountiful yield!

Germinate your seeds like pro growers

The key to unlock the highest potential yield all starts with a strong germination. The pro's keep it simple but consistent. Here is what we need, warmth, moisture, and darkness. Mastering the classic paper towel method can be your one-stop solution for germinating all your Cannabis Seeds. Plate the seeds between a piece of moist paper towel. Seal the towel in a plastic bag or container. And keep the bag/container in a warm but dark spot. Within a couple of days, you will see white taproots emerge from the seedlings.

Once the roots are about a centimeter long, gently transfer your seedlings into your growing medium. Becarefull not damaging the taproot and avoid touching the root all together. And make sure you use clean tools to avoid stunting the tap root. Damaging the root can ruin your grow. With a little bit of patience and care, you will have healthy sprouts ready to thrive!

Importance of soil

Soil is the foundation for every grow. Your soil provides the nutrients for your plants, which they need to develop strong roots and a lush growth. Rich soil with compost perlite and coco coir can carry your grow a long way. Adding some healthy soil support will be beneficial for your plants. Make sure you don't overdo it and keep the soil alive and balanced. With a little bit of love and care, your cannabis plants will reward you with the highest quality buds you can imagine.

Are special nutrients necessary

The short answer is no. Your cannabis plants can grow in basic soil. But nutrients can make a huge difference in the growth of your plants. We have a friend from Germany who makes his own nutrients and his grow always exceeds even our expectation. While we do not think it's easy to reproduce, his amazing grows. He does prove that having the right nutrients will make your cannabis plants thrive.
